version: 1
display_name: PHTN-50-000222 - The Photon operating system must be configured so that the x86 Ctrl-Alt-Delete key sequence is disabled on the command line.
global_description: |-
  When the Ctrl-Alt-Del target is enabled, a locally logged-on user who presses Ctrl-Alt-Delete, when at the console, can reboot the system. If accidentally pressed, as could happen in the case of a mixed OS environment, this can create the risk of short-term loss of systems availability due to unintentional reboot.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - PHTN-50-000222
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227
  cci:
    - CCI-000366
  nist:
    - CM-6 b
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_photon_5:
    type: custom
    desc: The Photon operating system must be configured so that the x86 Ctrl-Alt-Delete key sequence is disabled on the command line.
    control_id: PHTN-50-000222
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      At the command line, run the following command to verify the ctrl-alt-del target is disabled and masked:

      # systemctl status ctrl-alt-del.target --no-pager

      Example output:

      ctrl-alt-del.target
      \tLoaded: masked (Reason: Unit ctrl-alt-del.target is masked.)
      \tActive: inactive (dead)

      If the "ctrl-alt-del.target" is not "inactive" and "masked", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      When the Ctrl-Alt-Del target is enabled, a locally logged-on user who presses Ctrl-Alt-Delete, when at the console, can reboot the system. If accidentally pressed, as could happen in the case of a mixed OS environment, this can create the risk of short-term loss of systems availability due to unintentional reboot.
    remediation: |-
      At the command line, run the following commands:

      # systemctl disable ctrl-alt-del.target
      # systemctl mask ctrl-alt-del.target
      # systemctl daemon-reload
